# Copy to .env (or just `export` these) to run the real engine for FREE.
# The free providers are OpenAI-compatible, so only langchain-openai is needed.

# === PERSONAL (highest quality): Claude Opus =================================
# Paid (Anthropic API). Uses the native Anthropic client.
#   LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...        # console.anthropic.com
#   LLM_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8           # default; do NOT set temperature (Opus rejects it)

# === ANYONE, NO ACCOUNT, NO API KEY: local DeepSeek on your computer =========
# The optimal no-signup path: nothing leaves your machine, no key, fully offline.
#   1) Install Ollama (ollama.com)
#   2) ollama pull deepseek-r1:8b      # or deepseek-r1:1.5b on a low-end machine
#   3) set:
#   LLM_PROVIDER=ollama
#   LLM_MODEL=deepseek-r1:8b           # R1 reasoning; <think> traces auto-stripped
# Sizes: 1.5b (fast/weak) · 8b (balanced) · 14b/32b (strong, needs more RAM).
# Slow on old Intel Macs (CPU-only); great on Apple Silicon / any recent GPU.
# (Or set nothing at all -> zero-install MOCK demo mode anyone can run.)

# --- Pick ONE free hosted provider ------------------------------------------
# GROQ (recommended free tier): no credit card, fastest. Key at console.groq.com/keys
LLM_PROVIDER=groq
OPENAI_API_KEY=gsk_your_groq_key_here

# OPENROUTER (backup): free :free models. Key at openrouter.ai/keys
#   LLM_PROVIDER=openrouter
#   OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-or-your_key_here
#   LLM_MODEL=deepseek/deepseek-chat-v3:free   # pin a tool-calling :free model

# CEREBRAS (overflow, 1M tokens/day, 8K context cap): cloud.cerebras.ai
#   LLM_PROVIDER=cerebras
#   OPENAI_API_KEY=csk-your_key_here
#   LLM_MODEL=llama-3.1-8b     # NOTE: llama-3.3-70b is deprecated on Cerebras

# Real OpenAI (NOT free — needs prepaid credits):
#   LLM_PROVIDER=openai
#   OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# --- Optional: scrape a Job URL (else just paste the text — free) -----------
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=fc-...   # 1,000 free credits/month, firecrawl.dev

# --- Optional: real keyword job search for the Discover tab ------------------
# Free key at developer.adzuna.com. Without it, Discover uses the keyless feeds
# (Himalayas/Remotive/RemoteOK/company boards), which skew remote-tech. Adzuna
# adds real keyword search across all sectors (so niche roles like "SOC analyst"
# actually appear).
# ADZUNA_APP_ID=...
# ADZUNA_APP_KEY=...
# ADZUNA_COUNTRY=us
#
# JSearch (RapidAPI) — Google-for-Jobs aggregator: covers LinkedIn, Indeed,
# Glassdoor, ZipRecruiter etc. in one search. Free tier ~200 req/month, no card.
# Get a key at rapidapi.com/letscrape-6bRBa3QguO5/api/jsearch
# RAPIDAPI_KEY=...
#
# Reed.co.uk official Jobseeker API (UK-heavy, ~1000 req/day, free). Sanctioned —
# not scraping. Key at reed.co.uk/developers
# REED_API_KEY=...
#
# USAJOBS.gov official API (US federal jobs, free, cleanest ToS). Key at
# developer.usajobs.gov — needs the key AND the email you registered with.
# USAJOBS_API_KEY=...
# USAJOBS_EMAIL=you@example.com
#
# Jooble — broad aggregator incl. on-site & shift-based roles (SOC, healthcare,
# manufacturing). Free key at jooble.org/api/about
# JOOBLE_API_KEY=...
#
# Careerjet — broad on-site aggregator. Free affiliate id at careerjet.com/partners
# CAREERJET_AFFID=...
#
# Optional: bias keyword sources toward a location (Adzuna country is separate).
# JOB_LOCATION=Dallas, TX
# Track specific companies' boards (Greenhouse/Lever) in Discover:
# COMPANY_BOARDS=greenhouse:stripe,lever:netflix,greenhouse:airbnb

# --- Assisted apply (auto-fill, you submit) ---------------------------------
# The Apply card fills an application from your profile + tailored résumé and
# PAUSES at the Submit button (never auto-submits). Tracker + prepared packets
# work with nothing installed. To enable the browser auto-fill:
#   pip install playwright && playwright install chromium
# High-ban-risk boards (LinkedIn/Indeed/Glassdoor/Dice) are never automated —
# they fall back to a prepared packet + apply link you fill yourself.
# Where the tracker DB + saved résumés live (defaults shown):
# APPLY_DB=applications.sqlite
# APPLY_DIR=applications
